            <bug_when>2011-09-01 10:53:08 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>If a widget class custom.Foo extends e.g. qx.ui.form.Button, a qxh* locator step with the value &quot;qx.ui.form.Button&quot; should find it. This is currently not the case since instanceof checks will generally not work (apparently most browsers do not allow cross-window usage of instanceof). The fallback is a simple string comparison with the classname property. This should be extended so that it walks up the inheritance chain until it finds a matching class name or Object is reached.</thetext>
